# task #134 (tier-1 preamble): on a tier-1 config lodor_tier1_up brings tailscaled up from
# the PERSISTED login (no key, no QR) and is idempotent — the second call REUSES the running
# daemon (one daemon total). The wifi-debug log carries the honest transport verdict.
desc tier-1 preamble: lodor_tier1_up brings the tunnel up from persisted login, idempotently
invoke tslib
config tier1
tsdaemon slow:10
sdfile+ .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.state
tsdrv tier1up
tsdrv tier1up
tsdrv count
expect_exit 0
expect_trace TSDRV tier1up rc=0
expect_trace TSDRV daemons=1
expect_file_has .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.log tier-1 up: reusing persisted login
expect_file_has .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.log tailscaled already up; reusing
expect_file_has Tools/tg5040/Lodor.pak/wifi-debug.log tier1: tunnel up
